translated: Brandberg, Olof, qualified physician, from Trollhättan, born on January 1st, 1912 in Dannemora, Uppsala län, son of Nils B. and Vendela Ham-marskiöld. Married since 1939 to Margareta Brorström with whom he has three children: Asa born in 1940, Björn in 1942, and Kerstin in 1944. He completed his secondary education in Uppsala in 1930, and received a Bachelor of Medicine degree from Lund in 1934, and a medical licence in 1940. He worked as a temporary assistant doctor at various medical facilities including Malmö General Hospital surgical department and also at Sundsvalls Hospital surgical and medical departments from 1940 to 1941. In 1942, he had a temporary appointment as a district doctor in Bothby and Alnö and for two months he was a temporary assistant doctor at Nynäs Hospital. In addition, he worked as an assistant physician at Apelvikens Coastal Hospital in 1942-43, and had a temporary appointment as an assistant doctor at the surgical department of Varberg Hospital and the Kirurgiska avdelningen at Vänersborg Hospital and as a provisional medical doctor in the Alfredshem district in 1943. From 1943, he worked as a practicing physician in Trollhättan.
